      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: generate nvidia-style skill cards",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds V1 NVIDIA-style Skill Cards to ClawHub as generated Markdown artifacts. The product shape is intentionally artifact-first: ClawHub stores a generated `skill-card.md` on each skill version, renders it on the skill detail page, exposes it through HTTP, and provides a CLI verification endpoint/command.\n\n## Background and User Impact\n\nAgent skills are installable instruction bundles, so users need a clearer way to inspect provenance, release evidence, and scanner context before trusting a skill. Before this change, ClawHub had scan metadata and file hashes, but no generated human-facing Skill Card artifact tied to a release. Users also could not script against a single verification envelope, and `clawhub update` needed to keep working when generated release files like `skill-card.md` are included in installed bundles.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Adds a Skill Card generation queue that runs after static scan and ClawScan inputs have settled.\n- Builds a server-owned evidence packet containing publisher, server-resolved provenance, release data, file hashes, parsed metadata, capabilities, and ClawScan risk findings.\n- Reuses NVIDIA's public Skill Card tooling as the context-generation helper, then renders final public Markdown through a neutral ClawHub template to avoid NVIDIA-only boilerplate.\n- Stores generated cards as `skill-card.md` in `skillVersions.files` and replaces that file on regeneration for the same version.\n- Adds a generated bundle fingerprint after attaching the card while preserving the source fingerprint.\n- Lets `/api/v1/skills/resolve?slug=&hash=` match either the original source fingerprint or a generated bundle fingerprint.\n- Adds `/api/v1/skills/:slug/card?version=&tag=` for Markdown card retrieval.\n- Adds `/api/v1/skills/:slug/verify?version=&tag=` for JSON verification metadata.\n- Adds `clawhub skill verify <slug>`, with JSON as the default output and `--card` for raw Markdown.\n- Adds a Skill Card tab in the skill detail UI only when `skill-card.md` exists.\n- Adds local dev worker support so background workers can run in a normal local product loop.\n- Adds a GitHub Actions Skill Card worker triggered after the Security Scan Codex Worker completes, plus manual dispatch.\n\n## Security and Trust Boundaries\n\nProvenance remains fail-closed. The Skill Card evidence packet uses only server-resolved GitHub import provenance stored on the version; it does not trust author-claimed frontmatter or generic publish payload metadata. The CLI and `/verify` verdict use structured DB security metadata, not Markdown parsing.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch` clean after accepted fixes.\n- `bunx vitest run convex/lib/skillCards.test.ts convex/lib/skillPublish.test.ts --pool=forks --maxWorkers=2`\n- `bun run lint:oxlint -- convex/lib/skillCards.ts convex/lib/skillCards.test.ts convex/lib/skillPublish.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bun run ci:e2e-http`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n\n## Notes for Review\n\nThis deliberately avoids a rich formal trust-card schema in V1. The generated Markdown artifact is the product surface, with `/verify` serving as the scripting-oriented JSON surface.\n",
